[32m+[m[32m# ğŸ§¾ Git Branch Naming & Commit Message Guidelines[m
[32m+[m[32mTo maintain a clean and scalable Git history, follow these conventions for branch names and commit messages.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## ğŸš€ Branch Naming Convention[m
[32m+[m[32mUse the format:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m<branch-type>/<ticket-id>-<short-kebab-case-description>[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m### ğŸ”¹ Allowed Branch Types:[m
[32m+[m[32mType	Purpose[m
[32m+[m[32m- feat	-New feature[m
[32m+[m[32m- fix	Bug -fixes[m
[32m+[m[32m- refactor	-Code refactoring without behavior change[m
[32m+[m[32m- chore	-Misc tasks (e.g., updating config, scripts)[m
[32m+[m[32m- docs	-Documentation only[m
[32m+[m[32m- test	-Adding/updating tests[m
[32m+[m[32m- hotfix	-Emergency production fix[m
[32m+[m[32m- ui	-UI-only changes (pages, components, styles)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### ğŸ”¸ Examples:[m
[32m+[m[32mfeat/101-user-authentication[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfix/234-navbar-overlap-mobile[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mrefactor/119-reorganize-form-ho